# OctoAcme — UX Design & Collaboration

## Purpose
Define how UX design integrates into project execution and how UX Designers collaborate with other roles.

## When UX Design Starts
- **Project Planning Phase:** UX Designer involved in defining requirements and user flows
- **Sprint Planning:** Design specifications prepared before development begins
- **Development:** UX Designer reviews code and provides design feedback
- **QA:** UX Designer validates usability and design fidelity
- **Release:** UX Designer ensures help content and UI consistency

## Design Workflow

### 1. Requirements & Research
- UX Designer collaborates with Product Manager on user research
- Define user personas and user flows
- Identify accessibility and usability requirements
- Document design principles and constraints

### 2. Wireframes & Prototypes
- Create wireframes for user flows
- Build interactive prototypes for user testing
- Conduct usability testing with target users
- Gather feedback and iterate

### 3. Design Specifications
- Create detailed design specs with annotations
- Define UI component library and design tokens
- Document interaction patterns and animations
- Provide design assets (Figma, sketch files, etc.)

### 4. Development Handoff
- Share design specs with development team
- Conduct design review to confirm understanding
- Establish feedback loop for design questions
- Create design QA checklist

### 5. Design QA & Validation
- Review implemented features against design specs
- Validate responsive design across devices
- Confirm accessibility standards met (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Conduct usability testing on final implementation

## Design Review Checklist
- [ ] UI matches approved design specifications
- [ ] Responsive design works across breakpoints
- [ ] Accessibility standards met (keyboard navigation, screen readers, color contrast)
- [ ] Spacing, typography, and colors consistent with design system
- [ ] Error states and edge cases handled
- [ ] Loading and empty states designed
- [ ] Help text and labels clear
- [ ] Animations smooth and not distracting

## Collaboration Matrix
| Activity | UX Designer | Product Manager | Developer | QA Lead |
|----------|------------|-----------------|-----------|---------|
| User research | Lead | Support | — | — |
| Wireframing | Lead | Input | — | — |
| Design specs | Lead | Review | Implement | Validate |
| Design QA | Lead | Review | Address feedback | Co-validate |
| Help content | Input | Lead | — | Review |

## Design System & Component Library
- Maintain centralized design system (e.g., Storybook)
- Document component specs and usage guidelines
- Keep design system in sync with implementation
- Version design changes and communicate updates

## Accessibility Standards
All designs must meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA:
- [ ] Color contrast ratios (4.5:1 for text)
- [ ] Keyboard navigation support
- [ ] Screen reader compatibility
- [ ] Form labels and error messaging
- [ ] Focus indicators visible
- [ ] Motion/animation can be disabled

## Metrics & Validation
- Usability test results (task success rate, time on task)
- User satisfaction scores
- Support ticket volume related to UX confusion
- Feature adoption and engagement metrics